WEBVTT

00:01.523 --> 00:02.741
- Previously,
on "Falling Water"...

00:02.785 --> 00:05.005
- The Shadowman.

00:05.048 --> 00:09.618
- When my people get here,
I can explain everything.

00:10.967 --> 00:12.229
- Get in the car, now.

00:13.404 --> 00:14.797
- A search warrant.

00:14.840 --> 00:16.842
And a warrant for
your arrest, Mr. Hull.

00:16.886 --> 00:19.236
- Heard about all
the ruckus at the Firm.

00:19.280 --> 00:20.890
In the meantime,
I'd like to offer you a job.

00:20.933 --> 00:23.240
It's political,
straight up your alley.

00:23.284 --> 00:25.590
- Madam Mayor, Woody Hammond.

00:25.634 --> 00:26.983
I would like to
offer you my support.

00:27.027 --> 00:29.812
- That's very generous of you,
Mr. Hammond.

00:29.855 --> 00:31.683
- Tell her the
ball's in motion.

00:31.727 --> 00:34.643
- You did good, Burton,
you led us to a solid takedown.

00:34.686 --> 00:36.732
And who knows what the
evidence is gonna show

00:36.775 --> 00:38.429
or who else
it's gonna point to.

00:38.473 --> 00:40.692
- If someone else
was here, and recently,

00:40.736 --> 00:43.391
shouldn't we investigate it?
Isn't that what we do?

00:43.434 --> 00:45.871
And whoever set up camp
here drilled that hole

00:45.915 --> 00:48.483
to spy on the bedroom below
the night of the murder.

00:48.526 --> 00:50.224
Sam, you can make it stop.

00:51.442 --> 00:52.791
- I can't.

00:54.532 --> 00:56.317
- He won't let me.

01:01.583 --> 01:04.020
♪

01:04.064 --> 01:07.023
- No, no, no, no, no.

01:07.067 --> 01:08.851
No...no...

01:11.680 --> 01:14.465
What'd you do?

01:27.609 --> 01:34.616
♪

02:14.917 --> 02:18.747
♪

02:24.796 --> 02:30.106
♪

02:33.153 --> 02:38.941
♪

02:44.120 --> 02:45.687
- Police, ma'am.

02:48.777 --> 02:51.127
Where you headed?

02:51.171 --> 02:53.695
- Um, New York from Maine.

02:53.738 --> 02:59.614
Just needed to catch some
sleep before the final leg.

02:59.657 --> 03:03.792
- Might wanna spring
for a motel next time.

03:03.835 --> 03:05.968
You gotta be careful
where you sleep.

03:09.014 --> 03:15.107
♪

03:16.805 --> 03:18.110
- I'm sorry, Mom.

03:20.069 --> 03:21.810
- The Shadowman.

03:21.853 --> 03:23.507
He almost saw us.

03:23.551 --> 03:27.076
♪

03:30.122 --> 03:37.129
♪

03:40.394 --> 03:42.657
It doesn't make any sense.

03:42.700 --> 03:45.964
You know, why she would...

03:46.008 --> 03:48.663
Sabine is not a killer.

03:48.706 --> 03:50.186
- I know you loved her--

03:50.230 --> 03:54.538
- Love her.

03:54.582 --> 03:57.106
- She didn't want
your mom living here.

03:57.149 --> 04:01.502
- That's not a reason
to kill someone.

04:01.545 --> 04:04.635
- I'm not a shrink,
but I am a cop.

04:04.679 --> 04:09.031
You and I both know
sometimes people just snap.

04:09.074 --> 04:11.903
- You weren't there.

04:11.947 --> 04:15.733
She was standing here.

04:17.257 --> 04:20.129
Holding the bottle.

04:20.172 --> 04:25.961
Her eyes were open.

04:26.004 --> 04:29.878
And it's like--
it's like she couldn't see.

04:29.921 --> 04:32.881
She didn't even
hear the gagging.

04:32.924 --> 04:36.885
♪

04:36.928 --> 04:40.192
She's really gone.

04:40.236 --> 04:42.934
♪

04:46.938 --> 04:49.811
♪

04:49.854 --> 04:50.986
- I can't see this.

04:51.029 --> 04:53.031
- This man is dead.

04:53.075 --> 04:54.772
- The investigation is over,
Burton.

04:54.816 --> 04:55.904
- What in the hell
are you talking about?

04:55.947 --> 04:57.079
- We've got three indictments

04:57.122 --> 04:58.733
on corporate fraud,
case closed.

04:58.776 --> 05:00.256
- Hull-Bedford is responsible
for this man's death.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.258
- Has the NYPD come
to that conclusion?

05:02.302 --> 05:03.825
Because a dead body
is their jurisdiction.

05:03.868 --> 05:05.783
- No, it was staged
to look like an overdose.

05:05.827 --> 05:07.568
- My orders were clear--

05:07.611 --> 05:09.657
prosecute the financial
crimes we can make stick,

05:09.700 --> 05:13.138
that's it,
this comes from way up.

05:13.182 --> 05:16.185
If you get something solid--
and I mean airtight--

05:16.228 --> 05:20.929
you could directly
to a US attorney.

05:20.972 --> 05:22.931
- There's plenty
more evidence on this.

05:22.974 --> 05:24.193
- The case is over.

05:24.236 --> 05:26.282
I shouldn't even
be talking to you.

05:26.326 --> 05:28.937
- Hold on.

05:28.980 --> 05:31.505
Diane.

05:31.548 --> 05:33.071
- You're being investigated.

05:36.074 --> 05:38.294
- Embezzling.

05:38.338 --> 05:40.644
Hull-Bedford's attorneys
have provided evidence.

05:40.688 --> 05:42.037
- That's bullshit,
a retaliation.

05:42.080 --> 05:44.300
- I know,
that's why I'm telling you.

05:45.997 --> 05:52.134
♪

05:52.177 --> 05:54.310
- I'll take a look.
That's all I can do.

05:54.354 --> 05:56.181
- Thank you.

05:56.225 --> 05:57.792
- Watch your back.

05:57.835 --> 06:04.842
♪

06:08.150 --> 06:09.891
- Mayor Harding.

06:09.934 --> 06:12.328
- Thank you for coming on
such short notice, Mr. Hammond.

06:12.372 --> 06:13.808
- Always a pleasure to see you.

06:13.851 --> 06:17.202
- Sit, please.

06:22.904 --> 06:26.560
- Actually, you can't.

06:28.605 --> 06:30.781
- Have I done
something to offend you?

06:30.825 --> 06:33.958
- No, it's so stupid, I--

06:34.002 --> 06:35.830
I heard about the FBI raid.

06:35.873 --> 06:38.659
- Ah.

06:38.702 --> 06:40.182
Well...

06:40.225 --> 06:42.619
- These investigations
never amount to anything,

06:42.663 --> 06:46.057
but my advisors say
the optics aren't good.

06:46.101 --> 06:49.060
- And I suppose there's nothing
I can do to change your mind.

06:49.104 --> 06:52.107
- I so wish there was, but...

06:57.765 --> 06:59.680
- Well, there must be
a political action committee

06:59.723 --> 07:01.812
that supports you.

07:01.856 --> 07:06.382
Would optics keep them
from accepting this?

07:10.168 --> 07:11.866
Woody Hammond,

07:11.909 --> 07:14.303
has anyone ever suggested
you go into politics?

07:14.346 --> 07:17.262
♪

07:17.306 --> 07:19.003
- I see the laundry.

07:19.047 --> 07:21.963
- Okay, there's an alley
to the right of it.

07:22.006 --> 07:23.965
Follow that.

07:24.008 --> 07:31.015
♪

07:34.932 --> 07:36.760
- I remember you.

07:36.804 --> 07:39.241
- Well, the James I knew
was much shorter.

07:39.284 --> 07:41.025
Glad you're both safe.

07:41.069 --> 07:43.201
Come on.

07:43.245 --> 07:44.768
- I followed all
your instructions,

07:44.812 --> 07:46.683
parked four blocks away.

07:46.727 --> 07:48.163
You wanna tell me where we are?

07:48.206 --> 07:50.295
- Best Sudanese restaurant
in New York.

07:50.339 --> 07:53.690
Come, let's meet everyone.

07:53.734 --> 07:57.259
[utensils clanking,
restaurant chatter]

07:57.302 --> 08:01.132
- Grace, Clinton,
these are my friends.

08:01.176 --> 08:04.919
- Maybe Ronnie can be
a new friend to James.

08:04.962 --> 08:06.834
- He's a little tired
from the drive.

08:06.877 --> 08:08.879
- Maybe you'd like
a sweet first?

08:12.013 --> 08:14.972
Have you tried basboosa before?

08:18.410 --> 08:21.152
- In Sudan,
we also had to hide,

08:21.196 --> 08:23.067
until Burton
helped us immigrate.

08:23.111 --> 08:25.896
- I filled out a few forms,
that's all.

08:25.940 --> 08:27.942
- We would have died
if it wasn't for his help.

08:27.985 --> 08:30.161
- Well, now it's you and Grace
who are helping me.

08:30.205 --> 08:32.120
- It's the least we can do.

08:32.163 --> 08:33.774
You'll be safe here.

08:33.817 --> 08:36.298
- Thank you.

08:41.869 --> 08:46.221
- No one comes or goes
except through here.

08:48.876 --> 08:51.487
- I'm being watched.

08:53.445 --> 08:55.839
- The FBI.

08:57.493 --> 08:59.147
I thought you were
working with them.

08:59.190 --> 09:00.975
- Apparently not any longer.

09:01.018 --> 09:06.763
♪

09:07.982 --> 09:09.331
- Their hands are tied.

09:09.374 --> 09:10.854
There is one agent I trust.

09:10.898 --> 09:14.249
She's being watched too.

09:16.033 --> 09:17.992
- Hull-Bedford will do anything

09:18.035 --> 09:20.081
to protect their asses,
it seems.

09:20.124 --> 09:24.041
And their reach goes
further than I ever imagined.

09:24.085 --> 09:26.348
Look, it's not much,
but, um...

09:26.391 --> 09:28.045
- It's fine.

09:28.089 --> 09:29.786
Is Taka being watched too?

09:29.830 --> 09:32.006
Is that why he wouldn't
let me go to his place?

09:32.049 --> 09:35.183
- No, I told you not to go
because it's a crime scene.

09:38.055 --> 09:39.274
- Tell me.

09:39.317 --> 09:43.365
Tell me right now, Burton.

09:43.408 --> 09:45.759
- Your sister--

09:45.802 --> 09:48.370
it appears she murdered
Taka's mother.

09:48.413 --> 09:53.027
♪

09:53.070 --> 09:56.334
I'm sorry,
there's no easy way to say it.

09:56.378 --> 10:00.991
♪

10:01.035 --> 10:03.951
I don't understand it either.

10:03.994 --> 10:05.387
- No, there's been a mistake,

10:05.430 --> 10:07.476
there's just no way she...

10:07.519 --> 10:10.044
- It's no mistake.
She did it, Tess.

10:10.087 --> 10:11.219
Taka was there.

10:15.527 --> 10:18.574
- She can't answer because
she's been arrested.

10:18.618 --> 10:20.402
- You've reached the
confidential voicemail

10:20.445 --> 10:22.012
of Dr. Sabine Brighton.

10:22.056 --> 10:23.144
I can't come to
the phone right now.

10:24.188 --> 10:25.581
- Taka's going to come here

10:25.625 --> 10:28.497
after he's given his
statement to the authorities.

10:28.540 --> 10:32.849
- Did he say how she...

10:32.893 --> 10:35.896
- Chemical drain cleaner
down her throat.

10:35.939 --> 10:36.984
What?

10:37.027 --> 10:38.986
- I'm sorry.

10:39.029 --> 10:41.249
♪

10:41.292 --> 10:42.511
- It's not possible.

10:42.554 --> 10:43.904
- Listen, Tess, hey--

10:43.947 --> 10:45.906
- No, not my sister,
not Sabine.

10:45.949 --> 10:47.559
- Listen to me, the evidence--

10:47.603 --> 10:49.300
- I don't care
about the evidence.

10:49.344 --> 10:50.606
I'm telling you,
it's not possible.

10:50.650 --> 10:52.521
She's not capable
of something like that.

10:52.564 --> 10:54.523
- When Taka comes,
he'll explain everything.

10:54.566 --> 10:57.047
♪

10:59.310 --> 11:01.617
- Hey.

11:01.661 --> 11:04.576
- I'd crawl into bed
with her when we were kids,

11:04.620 --> 11:07.449
when I had a bad dream.

11:09.364 --> 11:11.496
She'd sing to me,

11:11.540 --> 11:15.283
anytime of the night,
so...

11:15.326 --> 11:17.328
so soft, so gentle.

11:19.940 --> 11:24.118
I'd fall right back to sleep.

11:24.161 --> 11:25.641
Oh, Sabine.

11:25.685 --> 11:29.210
- Hey, come here.

11:29.253 --> 11:30.907
Okay.

11:30.951 --> 11:32.953
♪

11:32.996 --> 11:34.998
Okay.

11:44.573 --> 11:45.487
- I just talked to her
a few days ago.

11:45.530 --> 11:50.884
She looked so happy.

11:50.927 --> 11:53.103
Taka, this makes no sense.

11:53.147 --> 11:54.757
Help me understand this.

11:54.801 --> 11:58.935
- How can I when I don't
understand it myself?

11:58.979 --> 12:00.720
- I'm so sorry.
I can't imagine.

12:02.156 --> 12:04.636
- Sabine went to see my mom,

12:04.680 --> 12:06.943
made sure the laundry
was being done, read to her.

12:08.684 --> 12:10.207
She was better with
my mom than I ever was.

12:10.251 --> 12:12.079
And then--

12:12.122 --> 12:15.952
- Why did you bring your mother
home from the care facility?

12:17.562 --> 12:19.651
- I, uh...

12:19.695 --> 12:23.655
I needed to dream with her.

12:23.699 --> 12:25.875
Why?

12:27.094 --> 12:29.705
- I have this case.

12:31.881 --> 12:33.970
Shit,
why didn't I see it before?

12:34.014 --> 12:36.146
- This the case where
the guy murdered his wife

12:36.190 --> 12:37.191
and he was dreaming?

12:37.234 --> 12:38.801
- Yes, damn, yes, okay,

12:38.845 --> 12:40.237
someone was in their attic--
a stranger.

12:40.281 --> 12:42.109
I have DNA evidence
to prove it.

12:42.152 --> 12:44.589
And I'm pretty sure
this person is a Dreamer.

12:44.633 --> 12:46.809
- A Dreamer who came
into this man's house

12:46.853 --> 12:48.202
to make him kill his wife?

12:48.245 --> 12:49.333
- I know it sounds crazy--

12:49.377 --> 12:50.813
- Doesn't sound any crazier

12:50.857 --> 12:52.684
than Sabine suddenly
turning into a murderer.

12:52.728 --> 12:54.034
- I don't know about that,
guys.

12:54.077 --> 12:56.340
- If it's true, if someone
else made her do it--

12:56.384 --> 12:58.168
- Look, at this point,
it's just a theory.

12:58.212 --> 12:59.604
We don't even have a suspect.

12:59.648 --> 13:00.910
- We need to talk to Sabine,

13:00.954 --> 13:02.956
find out if she remembers
any of her dreams.

13:02.999 --> 13:04.696
- She's at Central Booking.

13:04.740 --> 13:06.873
I can't even see her until
after she's arraigned.

13:08.222 --> 13:10.224
- Another day at least,
maybe two.

13:10.267 --> 13:13.009
I have a friend down there,
offered to get me in

13:13.053 --> 13:14.794
for a few minutes,
off the books.

13:14.837 --> 13:18.710
If anyone reported me,
I could lose my badge.

13:18.754 --> 13:21.278
- Could your friend arrange an
off

13:21.322 --> 13:24.368
- That's what I'm thinking.

13:25.848 --> 13:29.156
- You've got five minutes.

13:29.199 --> 13:30.374
- Tess.

13:30.418 --> 13:33.638
- Hey.

13:33.682 --> 13:35.945
- Thank you for coming.

13:37.904 --> 13:40.732
- You must be so scared.

13:40.776 --> 13:43.910
- I swear, I don't know
how any of this happened.

13:43.953 --> 13:45.737
I mean, I know that
I did it, but I--

13:45.781 --> 13:47.739
- Maybe you didn't do it,

13:47.783 --> 13:49.829
not on your own,

13:49.872 --> 13:52.179
We don't have much time.

13:52.222 --> 13:53.876
I heard you were
having nightmares.

13:53.920 --> 13:55.225
What were they about?

13:55.269 --> 13:57.053
- I already feel guilty enough.

13:57.097 --> 14:01.231
- This could help prove
you didn't intend to kill her.

14:01.275 --> 14:04.017
- I was having...

14:04.060 --> 14:05.888
nightmares about Kumiko.

14:07.194 --> 14:08.978
- "I doubt if I have
made the best use

14:09.022 --> 14:11.067
of all my calamities."

14:11.111 --> 14:13.156
They would start
normally enough.

14:13.200 --> 14:15.419
"Soft, amiable natures,

14:15.463 --> 14:18.248
they would've refined
to saintliness."

14:18.292 --> 14:20.772
You are no saint.

14:20.816 --> 14:25.734
You are selfish
and conniving.

14:25.777 --> 14:28.868
You stole him from me!

14:28.911 --> 14:29.912
- I didn't.

14:29.956 --> 14:31.871
- Liar!

14:31.914 --> 14:35.091
- She looked the same,
but evil.

14:35.135 --> 14:37.920
And she'd say
horrible things to me.

14:37.964 --> 14:41.924
♪

14:41.968 --> 14:44.753
- You'd like to squash me
like a cockroach

14:44.796 --> 14:47.974
so you can have him
all to yourself.

14:48.017 --> 14:50.802
- Did you actually
see cockroaches?

14:52.326 --> 14:53.457
- Yes.

14:54.850 --> 14:57.287
- From everywhere.

14:57.331 --> 15:00.334
♪

15:03.380 --> 15:08.255
♪

15:08.298 --> 15:11.127
- Was there anyone else
in the dream?

15:11.171 --> 15:13.738
- There was a man, um,

15:13.782 --> 15:16.132
something upstairs.

15:16.176 --> 15:23.183
♪

15:27.013 --> 15:32.148
- What did he look like,
that man upstairs?

15:32.192 --> 15:34.063
- I'm not sure.

15:37.849 --> 15:40.852
♪

15:40.896 --> 15:43.029
- Just like this.

15:45.857 --> 15:48.948
- James calls him
the Shadowman.

15:50.427 --> 15:54.040
It was just...a dream.

15:54.083 --> 15:55.867
My dream.

15:55.911 --> 15:58.174
It only proves
how much I hated her.

15:58.218 --> 15:59.828
- Of course you
didn't hate her.

15:59.871 --> 16:01.961
- I did.

16:02.004 --> 16:03.527
That's what scares me.

16:03.571 --> 16:05.399
She was--

16:05.442 --> 16:09.881
I would wake up,
and I'd feel this rage.

16:09.925 --> 16:13.363
She was totally helpless,
she couldn't even speak, and...

16:13.407 --> 16:16.062
it made me
hate her even more.

16:19.108 --> 16:20.849
- Time's up.

16:22.851 --> 16:25.201
- Tell Taka.

16:25.245 --> 16:26.898
Tell him...

16:26.942 --> 16:30.380
I'm sorry.

16:30.424 --> 16:33.557
- I'm gonna find a way
to get you out of here.

16:33.601 --> 16:34.906
I will.
- Let's go.

16:34.950 --> 16:41.957
♪

16:46.570 --> 16:48.311
- Thanks for putting me up.

16:48.355 --> 16:50.052
It shouldn't be
more than day or two

16:50.096 --> 16:51.401
before I'm back
into my own place.

16:51.445 --> 16:53.403
- Can't imagine
it'll be easy going back.

16:53.447 --> 16:56.319
- The main thing now is
to figure out what happened.

16:56.363 --> 16:58.104
Tess doesn't know
anything about

16:58.147 --> 16:59.453
the Morrison murder.

16:59.496 --> 17:01.020
She's not gonna know
what to ask Sabine,

17:01.063 --> 17:02.891
what details are important.

17:02.934 --> 17:05.154
- You don't actually
know they're connected.

17:05.198 --> 17:08.462
- You're right, I don't.
I have a feeling.

17:08.505 --> 17:10.420
- Now so does Tess.

17:10.464 --> 17:12.553
Did you stop to think you
might be giving her false hope?

17:12.596 --> 17:14.294
- Like I said,
it's just a theory.

17:14.337 --> 17:15.947
- A theory Tess thinks
might exonerate her sister,

17:15.991 --> 17:18.080
but it can't, can it?

17:18.124 --> 17:19.429
Yeah, but,

17:19.473 --> 17:20.604
if she wasn't acting
of her own free will,

17:20.648 --> 17:21.953
if she was coerced--

17:21.997 --> 17:23.216
- In her dreams,

17:23.259 --> 17:24.521
by another Dreamer,
to commit murder?

17:24.565 --> 17:26.001
- I know it sounds crazy,

17:26.045 --> 17:27.481
but you've seen firsthand

17:27.524 --> 17:29.309
how dangerous dreams can be.

17:29.352 --> 17:32.094
- Okay, maybe some Dreamers
can force someone to kill.

17:32.138 --> 17:33.443
I've never seen it,
neither has Tess.

17:33.487 --> 17:35.228
But now she's
at the police station

17:35.271 --> 17:36.881
because she desperately
wants to believe it's true.

17:36.925 --> 17:38.970
- Morrison said he was
having a nightmare.

17:39.014 --> 17:42.017
Hey, I found evidence someone
was sleeping in the attic.

17:42.061 --> 17:43.410
- We're not talking
about Morrison,

17:43.453 --> 17:47.066
we're talking about
Tess and Sabine and you.

17:47.109 --> 17:49.155
Taka, look,
this theory of yours

17:49.198 --> 17:51.200
is giving all
three of you hope.

17:51.244 --> 17:53.289
I'm not really sure it helps.

17:53.333 --> 17:54.899
- You're right.

17:54.943 --> 17:56.466
Theories don't help--

17:56.510 --> 17:57.641
evidence does.

18:00.688 --> 18:02.472
♪

18:07.347 --> 18:14.354
♪

18:44.210 --> 18:51.217
♪

18:53.001 --> 18:53.958
Ah--jeez!

18:55.482 --> 18:57.440
- I told you if you
followed me, I'd kill you.

18:57.484 --> 18:58.485
- Ah--

18:58.528 --> 18:59.573
- I won't tell you again--

18:59.616 --> 19:01.923
stay away from me and my son.

19:17.460 --> 19:24.032
♪

19:29.429 --> 19:36.436
♪

19:46.010 --> 19:49.013
[sirens wailing
and chirping]

19:49.057 --> 19:56.020
♪

19:59.067 --> 20:03.114
♪

20:06.161 --> 20:13.168
♪

20:19.522 --> 20:21.394
- You're supposed
to be taking time off.

20:21.437 --> 20:23.570
- Just look, this RV
pulled in a little after 3:00,

20:23.613 --> 20:26.268
and it pulled away
at 5:44 a.m.,

20:26.312 --> 20:28.618
exactly two minutes after
I placed the call to 911,

20:28.662 --> 20:31.447
- Okay, so someone on
your block works first shift.

20:31.491 --> 20:34.189
- No one ever got in or out.

20:34.233 --> 20:36.278
- You are on bereavement
leave.

20:36.322 --> 20:38.280
- The Morrisons had an attic.
My building doesn't.

20:38.324 --> 20:40.413
But that RV parked
in the same spot,

20:40.456 --> 20:41.805
three nights in a row--
- Taka.

20:41.849 --> 20:43.067
- I mean,
it could've been weeks,

20:43.111 --> 20:44.373
but the store owner deleted

20:44.417 --> 20:46.636
a bunch of video files
over the weekend.

20:46.680 --> 20:49.204
- Okay.

20:50.510 --> 20:52.163
When was the last time
you ate

20:52.207 --> 20:54.340
or slept?

20:54.383 --> 20:55.341
- I'm fine.

20:55.384 --> 20:56.690
- No, you're not.

20:56.733 --> 20:59.301
Maybe you should
talk to Doc Vickers.

20:59.345 --> 21:01.303
- What if someone was sleeping
outside my building,

21:01.347 --> 21:03.305
just like someone was sleeping
in the Morrisons' attic?

21:03.349 --> 21:06.308
This would be proof.

21:09.180 --> 21:11.182
Look, I'm...

21:11.226 --> 21:12.662
I'm not crazy.

21:12.706 --> 21:15.186
- I know you're not crazy,
but I'm worried about you.

21:17.363 --> 21:19.321
- Will you please just

21:19.365 --> 21:21.671
run the plates?

21:21.715 --> 21:24.283
I can't work on the case.

21:24.326 --> 21:28.504
♪

21:28.548 --> 21:30.854
- Okay.

21:30.898 --> 21:32.465
I'll run the plates
if you promise

21:32.508 --> 21:33.857
to talk to Doc Vickers.

21:33.901 --> 21:35.816
Final offer.

21:35.859 --> 21:41.865
♪

21:41.909 --> 21:43.824
- Deal.

21:43.867 --> 21:51.092
♪

21:55.662 --> 21:58.795
♪

22:01.929 --> 22:03.365
- Hey.

22:03.409 --> 22:05.236
There are more
basboosa downstairs

22:05.280 --> 22:06.455
if you eat lunch.

22:06.499 --> 22:08.805
- No, thanks.

22:10.546 --> 22:12.374
Long couple of days.

22:12.418 --> 22:15.464
Probably didn't get
much sleep in the car.

22:15.508 --> 22:17.292
- I'm not tired.

22:18.380 --> 22:21.340
- Ronnie's a nice boy,
isn't he?

22:21.383 --> 22:23.907
- He's at school.

22:23.951 --> 22:25.431
She--

22:25.474 --> 22:27.520
she shouldn't have
made us leave Maine.

22:28.869 --> 22:31.524
A mom isn't
supposed to do that.

22:34.353 --> 22:37.486
- My dad died when I was ten,

22:37.530 --> 22:39.662
and my mother and I
had to leave London

22:39.706 --> 22:40.924
and go to live
with my grandparents

22:40.968 --> 22:43.405
in a place called Bristol.

22:43.449 --> 22:45.233
I hated it.

22:45.276 --> 22:47.801
Everything was different.

22:47.844 --> 22:50.412
- Both of our moms
should've never made us move.

22:50.456 --> 22:52.545
- They did it
to keep us safe.

22:52.588 --> 22:53.937
That's what mums do.

22:53.981 --> 22:55.286
It's their job.

22:55.330 --> 22:58.507
- She is my real mom,
isn't she?

22:58.551 --> 23:00.727
- James,

23:00.770 --> 23:02.424
no one but your real mum

23:02.468 --> 23:07.777
would've done what
she did to find you.

23:07.821 --> 23:09.605
Why don't you lay down
for a bit, hm?

23:09.649 --> 23:11.302
Your mum will be home soon.

23:11.346 --> 23:12.956
I guarantee you'll be asleep

23:13.000 --> 23:14.741
before I get down
to the kitchen.

23:14.784 --> 23:17.439
- I don't wanna
see him again.

23:20.660 --> 23:22.923
James?

23:22.966 --> 23:25.316
Who are you afraid of?

23:25.360 --> 23:27.449
- I can show you.

23:30.321 --> 23:32.672
All right, then.

23:36.371 --> 23:43.378
♪

23:44.814 --> 23:47.600
- Don't let him see you.

23:47.643 --> 23:54.607
♪

24:04.007 --> 24:10.971
♪

24:14.017 --> 24:21.242
♪

24:34.037 --> 24:36.387
- Shh.

24:36.431 --> 24:43.438
♪

25:00.716 --> 25:03.893
Bloody hell.

25:03.937 --> 25:05.373
You okay?

25:05.416 --> 25:09.595
♪

25:28.788 --> 25:30.050
- Amelia.

25:30.093 --> 25:32.748
Amelia. You do not have
to tell me what's wrong,

25:32.792 --> 25:34.445
but you do not
walk away from me.

25:34.489 --> 25:35.751
- I have homework.

25:35.795 --> 25:36.752
Oh.

25:36.796 --> 25:39.363
- Wait.

25:44.020 --> 25:45.587
- Excuse me, young lady.

25:45.631 --> 25:46.936
You know better than this.

25:46.980 --> 25:48.372
Amel--

25:48.416 --> 25:49.591
Excuse me, missy.

25:49.635 --> 25:52.551
- I'm not talking to you.

26:01.951 --> 26:07.827
♪

26:09.176 --> 26:11.526
♪

26:12.745 --> 26:14.398
- Mmm, yeah.

26:16.444 --> 26:18.489
- The Edelman fundraiser
starts in five minutes,

26:18.533 --> 26:20.622
and we're 50,000 below goal.

26:20.666 --> 26:22.406
- ♪ Hey you

26:22.450 --> 26:25.409
- Uh...

26:25.453 --> 26:28.978
I should get dressed.

26:29.022 --> 26:30.719
You can't be here,
people will see.

26:30.763 --> 26:32.808
- Look, you're the one
who wanted to do it there.

26:32.852 --> 26:34.505
Deep down,
you're an exhibitionist.

26:34.549 --> 26:35.811
Embrace it.

26:35.855 --> 26:37.813
- Just find my clothes,
please?

26:40.207 --> 26:42.513
Tell the Edelmans
I'll be on my way.

26:42.557 --> 26:44.646
- Waste of a good sex dream,
if you ask me.

26:44.690 --> 26:51.174
♪

26:52.698 --> 26:55.178
♪

26:55.222 --> 26:57.616
It's all I could find.

26:57.659 --> 27:03.839
♪

27:03.883 --> 27:05.667
So, are we going
to the shindig together?

27:05.711 --> 27:06.755
- Put that on.

27:06.799 --> 27:08.801
- If you insist.

27:11.020 --> 27:12.718
- Amelia.

27:12.761 --> 27:13.980
What are you doing here?

27:14.023 --> 27:16.547
You're supposed
to be in school.

27:16.591 --> 27:18.593
- No.

27:19.986 --> 27:21.727
- No one.

27:21.770 --> 27:24.207
Mr. Hammond is a
contributor to the campaign.

27:24.251 --> 27:26.862
- Oh, did he contribute
his pants too?

27:26.906 --> 27:29.038
- You're being very
inappropriate, young lady.

27:29.082 --> 27:31.867
- Are you gonna tell dad it's
"another" surprise pregnancy?

27:31.911 --> 27:33.564
- Amelia!

27:35.654 --> 27:38.134
- We will talk
about this later.

27:38.178 --> 27:44.967
♪

27:46.665 --> 27:48.101
- Voila.

27:48.144 --> 27:49.624
There you go.

27:55.282 --> 27:56.892
- I don't like the crusts.

27:59.242 --> 28:01.984
Well, that's a problem
that is easily solved.

28:03.246 --> 28:06.597
But my mum always
used to say...

28:09.992 --> 28:11.559
This is Burton.

28:11.602 --> 28:13.169
- Have you looked
at the news?

28:15.694 --> 28:17.173
- Take a look,

28:17.217 --> 28:19.741
then realize how much
danger you're in.

28:27.314 --> 28:33.842
♪

28:38.020 --> 28:39.239
- Your mom.

28:39.282 --> 28:42.633
What did she say?

28:42.677 --> 28:46.681
- Oh, that the crust
has all the vitamins.

28:46.725 --> 28:50.293
♪

28:50.337 --> 28:52.861
- That's one lucky dog.

28:52.905 --> 28:55.777
- No, Woody.

28:55.821 --> 28:57.692
I'm the lucky one.

28:57.736 --> 28:59.781
Brutus is the
perfect companion.

28:59.825 --> 29:03.002
He knows all,
but tells no one.

29:03.045 --> 29:06.048
You, on the other hand,
are paid to tell me everything.

29:08.834 --> 29:10.574
- If you don't mind my asking,

29:10.618 --> 29:13.142
the mayor's a smart,
successful woman,

29:13.186 --> 29:15.144
like you.

29:15.188 --> 29:19.583
I can't help but wonder
why you're not backing her.

29:19.627 --> 29:21.890
- You growing attached
to Elizabeth Harding, Woody?

29:21.934 --> 29:23.805
- Of course not.

29:23.849 --> 29:25.981
- Wouldn't be the first.

29:26.025 --> 29:29.942
It's one of the perils of
having such intimate contact.

29:29.985 --> 29:32.683
It can be difficult
to remain unencumbered.

29:32.727 --> 29:35.817
- Unencumbered is my
specialty.

29:35.861 --> 29:39.690
- That's your reputation.

29:39.734 --> 29:41.823
I need results.

29:41.867 --> 29:43.346
- And I need
a little more time.

29:43.390 --> 29:46.349
If I can verify
what I saw last night,

29:46.393 --> 29:49.744
I promise it will be
the end of her career.

29:49.788 --> 29:51.877
- Good.

29:51.920 --> 29:55.010
Success is always rewarded.

29:55.054 --> 29:57.708
Just ask Brutus.

29:57.752 --> 30:00.146
Good boy, good boy.

30:14.682 --> 30:15.726
- Hey.

30:18.947 --> 30:21.254
Take that as a no.

30:21.297 --> 30:22.995
- I will.

30:23.038 --> 30:24.866
- Yeah, you'd better.

30:24.910 --> 30:26.389
I ran those plates.

30:27.738 --> 30:28.957
- They're stolen.

30:29.001 --> 30:32.178
Taken a couple weeks ago
off an old Buick.

30:35.050 --> 30:36.356
- Someone went to
a lot of trouble

30:36.399 --> 30:38.358
putting stolen plates on.

30:38.401 --> 30:40.186
- Yeah, I wouldn't get
your hopes up too high.

30:40.229 --> 30:41.752
It's probably nothing.
But I went ahead

30:41.796 --> 30:43.363
and put out a BOLO
on the RV anyway.

30:43.406 --> 30:45.060
Every unit in the city's

30:45.104 --> 30:46.409
looking for that heap,
all right?

30:46.453 --> 30:48.063
- Man, thanks for running
the plates, Alex.

30:48.107 --> 30:49.891
Seriously.
- Of course.

30:52.067 --> 30:54.722
There's no shame in talking
to someone, you know.

30:54.765 --> 30:58.421
- I'll call Vickers, I promise.

30:58.465 --> 31:00.815
All right, thanks.

31:00.859 --> 31:03.905
♪

31:11.913 --> 31:12.435
- The case has been
all over the news.

31:13.654 --> 31:14.829
- He keeps saying,
they just wanna talk.

31:14.873 --> 31:16.439
Sound familiar?

31:16.483 --> 31:18.050
I'll give you one guess
who I think it is.

31:18.093 --> 31:20.095
both: Bill Boerg.
- Exactly.

31:20.139 --> 31:21.923
- Boerg did try
to take James before.

31:21.967 --> 31:23.794
- The only problem with
that theory is Boerg seems

31:23.838 --> 31:25.361
to have disappeared
off the face of the Earth.

31:25.405 --> 31:26.928
- Uh-huh.

31:26.972 --> 31:28.799
It was in all the financials.
He divested himself

31:28.843 --> 31:32.107
of all his businesses,
holdings and just disappeared.

31:32.151 --> 31:33.674
- Wow.

31:33.717 --> 31:35.937
- No, more likely,
it's Hull-Bedford.

31:35.981 --> 31:37.634
- Mm-hmm.

31:37.678 --> 31:39.071
- Wouldn't they just
come and kidnap us

31:39.114 --> 31:40.637
in the middle of the night?
- True enough.

31:40.681 --> 31:42.378
Subtlety
is not their strong suit.

31:42.422 --> 31:43.379
Still.

31:44.990 --> 31:47.383
- My life was threatened today.

31:48.558 --> 31:49.864
- And they fished the FBI agent

31:49.908 --> 31:50.952
I was working with
out of the Hudson.

31:50.996 --> 31:52.911
- Oh, shit.

31:53.999 --> 31:56.044
It's happening all over again.
Shit!

31:56.088 --> 31:57.654
I have to get James.

31:57.698 --> 31:58.960
- Tess.

31:59.004 --> 32:00.657
- Well,
we can't stay all together

32:00.701 --> 32:02.833
in the same spot, Burton,
it's too dangerous.

32:02.877 --> 32:04.487
- Listen to me,

32:04.531 --> 32:06.141
Taka and I promised you
we'd keep you safe.

32:06.185 --> 32:07.708
- That's right.
- And we will.

32:09.536 --> 32:11.755
Lo-look what happened to
Sabine, to your mother.

32:11.799 --> 32:14.019
Now your FBI agent?

32:14.062 --> 32:15.846
And now
there's this crazy tutor

32:15.890 --> 32:17.848
running after James and me?
- You need to believe me.

32:17.892 --> 32:19.502
Right now,

32:19.546 --> 32:20.982
this is the
safest place for you to be.

32:21.026 --> 32:23.767
Really.

32:23.811 --> 32:26.683
- Except then there's this.

32:29.730 --> 32:31.166
♪

32:31.210 --> 32:33.821
James calls him the Shadowman.

32:36.084 --> 32:37.520
- I've seen him.

32:37.564 --> 32:39.000
- Yeah, me too.

32:39.044 --> 32:40.523
- In the dreams.

32:40.567 --> 32:41.698
James showed him to me.

32:41.742 --> 32:43.526
- And my mother showed me.

32:43.570 --> 32:45.920
- Sabine saw him
in her dream before she--

32:48.140 --> 32:50.185
- Shadowman.

32:50.229 --> 32:54.189
- Even if we can stay safe
here in the real world,

32:54.233 --> 32:57.018
how do we protect
ourselves from this thing

32:57.062 --> 32:59.716
coming after us
in our dreams?

33:03.068 --> 33:04.504
- Hey, sweetie.

33:07.768 --> 33:10.727
- Yeah, everything's fine.

33:10.771 --> 33:12.555
Go back on down,
I'll be there in a second.

33:12.599 --> 33:13.774
- All right, bye, Mom.

33:13.817 --> 33:15.689
- Mm-hmm.

33:21.042 --> 33:22.565
- I don't think it's a thing.

33:22.609 --> 33:24.045
I think it's an actual person.

33:24.089 --> 33:26.047
- Yeah, I think so.

33:26.091 --> 33:27.570
And there was an RV parked

33:27.614 --> 33:29.050
in front of my
building that night.

33:29.094 --> 33:31.009
It had stolen plates,
and whoever this Dreamer is,

33:31.052 --> 33:33.054
I think he or she
was sleeping there

33:33.098 --> 33:34.751
to get in Sabine's dreams.

33:35.883 --> 33:37.493
- Or the closer he is,

33:37.537 --> 33:38.929
the more easily he
can control someone.

33:38.973 --> 33:40.235
- Wait,
does that mean he was here?

33:40.279 --> 33:41.236
- Shadowman didn't come to us.

33:41.280 --> 33:43.238
James led me to him.

33:43.282 --> 33:44.848
- Same with me.

33:44.892 --> 33:46.763
- Yeah, my mother showed
the Shadowman to me.

33:46.807 --> 33:49.201
- Okay, so, high level Dreamers
like James and your mother

33:49.244 --> 33:51.507
can, what, sense this bastard?

33:51.551 --> 33:53.118
- If that's true,

33:53.161 --> 33:54.945
then James knows
how to find him,

33:54.989 --> 33:56.077
which means he could
lead me to him.

33:56.121 --> 33:57.992
- No, not happening.

33:58.036 --> 33:59.559
- Tess.
- No.

33:59.602 --> 34:00.951
- Even if it could prove
Sabine's innocent?

34:00.995 --> 34:02.214
I mean,
don't you care about that?

34:02.257 --> 34:03.519
- Of course I do.

34:03.563 --> 34:04.999
We're not using my son as bait

34:05.043 --> 34:07.088
for some psycho dream killer.

34:10.135 --> 34:14.095
♪

34:21.581 --> 34:23.887
- Mom, look,
they're real flowers.

34:27.021 --> 34:29.067
- I love the smell.

34:30.764 --> 34:33.723
- Ronnie says this is the last
thing they do every night--

34:33.767 --> 34:35.638
make tea for the next day.

34:37.814 --> 34:40.121
- I'm glad you like it here.

34:40.165 --> 34:42.080
- Except for all the boxes.

34:42.123 --> 34:44.212
- We'll fix it up.

34:44.256 --> 34:45.953
- Does that mean we're--

34:45.996 --> 34:48.912
we're never going home?

34:48.956 --> 34:51.654
- I'm sorry we had
to leave Maine, sweetie.

34:51.698 --> 34:53.743
There was no other choice.

34:53.787 --> 34:55.658
- I know.

34:55.702 --> 34:57.747
You just wanna keep me safe.

34:57.791 --> 34:59.880
You're my mom.

34:59.923 --> 35:02.535
That is your job.

35:04.102 --> 35:07.235
- That's right.

35:07.279 --> 35:11.152
And that's why I need you
to stop looking for Shadowman.

35:11.196 --> 35:12.849
- But Mom,

35:12.893 --> 35:15.852
he's very angry and
wants to hurt people,

35:15.896 --> 35:18.594
lots of people.

35:18.638 --> 35:20.596
- Let's let Taka and Burton
deal with him.

35:20.640 --> 35:23.164
- But...

35:23.208 --> 35:26.080
I know where he is.

35:26.124 --> 35:28.300
You won't be able
to find him without me.

35:28.343 --> 35:30.563
I can help.

35:33.087 --> 35:35.263
- I know you wanna help,
but...

35:35.307 --> 35:37.700
- Mom,

35:37.744 --> 35:39.746
I can do this.

35:41.226 --> 35:43.141
He needs to be stopped.

35:43.184 --> 35:48.711
♪

35:50.887 --> 35:53.890
♪

35:57.807 --> 35:59.418
- So,
if this Shadowman's a Dreamer,

35:59.461 --> 36:01.724
that means he's a real person
with flesh and blood,

36:01.768 --> 36:02.856
like you and me.

36:03.509 --> 36:04.466
Now, if we can find him,
we might be able

36:05.685 --> 36:07.991
to figure out where
he is in the real world.

36:08.035 --> 36:11.430
- You don't have to do anything
you don't wanna do, James.

36:11.473 --> 36:13.475
- I know.

36:13.519 --> 36:15.651
- Let's get to it, then.

36:18.698 --> 36:23.529
♪

36:24.921 --> 36:31.928
♪

36:39.066 --> 36:45.725
♪

36:45.768 --> 36:47.770
- Well, this is different.

36:47.814 --> 36:54.864
♪

36:56.866 --> 37:02.045
♪

37:02.089 --> 37:04.526
- I can't tell you why
I feel this, but...

37:04.570 --> 37:05.875
I think it's us.

37:07.486 --> 37:14.536
♪

37:21.369 --> 37:24.372
[train rumbling,
wheels grinding]

37:24.416 --> 37:26.896
♪

37:26.940 --> 37:29.377
- He's up there.

37:29.421 --> 37:31.858
♪

37:31.901 --> 37:34.730
- I know this place.
- Me too.

37:34.774 --> 37:36.906
- Yep.

37:39.953 --> 37:46.960
♪

37:58.406 --> 38:05.457
♪

38:35.400 --> 38:38.141
♪

38:41.188 --> 38:45.714
♪

38:45.758 --> 38:47.847
- I see you.
- I see you.

38:47.890 --> 38:50.850
- I see you.

38:50.893 --> 38:52.155
- I see you.

38:52.199 --> 38:54.897
- I see you!

38:54.941 --> 38:56.856
- I see you.

38:56.899 --> 38:58.074
- I see you.
- I see you.

39:00.425 --> 39:02.383
- I see you.

39:02.427 --> 39:04.124
- I see you.
- I see you.

39:04.167 --> 39:06.996
- I see you.

39:07.040 --> 39:09.608
- I see you.
- I see you.

39:09.651 --> 39:13.089
- I see you.

39:16.136 --> 39:23.143
♪

39:30.063 --> 39:31.717
- Change of plan.

39:31.760 --> 39:33.153
Let's get out of here.

39:33.196 --> 39:35.721
- No!

39:42.728 --> 39:48.908
♪

39:48.951 --> 39:52.215
- I know none of us
wanted any of this,

39:52.259 --> 39:54.740
but we need to figure out
how to stop this guy.

39:54.783 --> 39:56.481
- We found him,
